# Matriarch - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Java library implementing the Object Mother pattern for test data generation. Published to Maven Central as dev.agiro:matriarch.

## Tech Stack
- Java 21 (no Lombok), Maven (./mvnw), JUnit 5
- Dependencies: Jackson, SnakeYAML, Reflections

## Project Structure
- `src/main/java/dev/agiro/matriarch/domain/core/` - Core generation logic, reflection cache
- `src/main/java/dev/agiro/matriarch/domain/model/` - Domain entities (Overrider, Definition, Coordinate)
- `src/main/java/dev/agiro/matriarch/generators/` - Type-specific data generation strategies
- `src/main/java/dev/agiro/matriarch/infrastructure/` - Pattern loading (YAML, System Properties)
- `src/main/java/dev/agiro/matriarch/junit/` - JUnit 5 extensions and annotations
- `src/main/java/dev/agiro/matriarch/suppliers/` - Smart data suppliers by category
- `src/main/java/dev/agiro/matriarch/util/` - TypeReference and utilities

## Conventions
- No Lombok — this is a published library with no external annotation processors
- Entry point: Mother.forClass(T.class) → fluent builder → .build()
- forField() is the preferred API; override() is a legacy alias
- Suppliers organized by domain: address, company, datetime, financial, internet, numeric, personal, text, util
- Override precedence: forField value > forField supplier > forType supplier > pattern matching > random
- Maintain backward compatibility for all public API changes
- Keep dependency footprint minimal — do not add dependencies without careful consideration
- Tests in object_samples/ contain varied POJOs (records, inheritance, generics, static factories)

## Build Commands
- Build + test: ./mvnw clean install
- Tests only: ./mvnw test
- Package: ./mvnw package
